  _changelogEntries:
  - version: Release 1.0
    year: 2024
    month: 11
    day: 3
    details: "The first release of Sortify provides a streamlined toolset to enhance
      your Unity workflow, focusing on organization and customization within the
      project hierarchy. Below is a summary of the core features available in this
      version:\n\nKey Features in Basic Version\n\u2022 Color Coding for Objects:
      Easily assign colors to objects in the hierarchy, improving visual organization
      and making important items stand out.\n\u2022 Personal Notes: Attach notes
      to objects directly in the hierarchy to organize project details and keep track
      of essential information.\n\u2022 Quick Add for Components: Quickly add frequently
      used components directly from the hierarchy, saving time and boosting efficiency.\n\u2022
      Basic Custom Attributes: Utilize basic attributes like toggles and headers
      to create more organized Inspector layouts.\n\nQuality of Life Improvements\n\u2022
      Optimized Hierarchy Performance: This version is optimized for smooth navigation,
      even in large scenes.\n\u2022 Local Data Storage: Sortify saves user-specific
      settings locally, allowing for customization without affecting project files."
  - version: 1.05 Hotfix
    year: 2024
    month: 11
    day: 25
    details: "\u2022 Fixed an issue occurring after changing the Build Target.\n\u2022
      Fixed a display bug for component icons in the hierarchy."
  - version: 1.1
    year: 2024
    month: 12
    day: 2
    details: "New Features\n\u2022 Highlight Module: Added object highlighting when
      hovering over it in the hierarchy, making it easier to locate objects in the
      scene.\n\nBug Fixes\n\u2022 Addressed several other minor bugs to improve overall
      stability and performance."
  - version: 1.2
    year: 2024
    month: 12
    day: 23
    details: "New Attributes\n\u2022 Layer Attribute\r\n\u2022 Tag Attribute\r\n\u2022
      Unit Attribute\r\n\u2022 Validate Attribute\n\nBug Fixes\n\u2022 Resolved a
      problem with the Button attribute. It now also works in Scriptable Objects.\n\u2022
      Improved the saving mechanism for hierarchy settings."
  - version: 1.25 Hotfix
    year: 2025
    month: 1
    day: 9
    details: "\u2022 Fixed a critical issue with saving certain object settings in
      the hierarchy. Detailed explanation of the issue is available on Discord.\n\u2022
      Object settings are no longer displayed in Play Mode. A message \"Play Mode
      Active - Simplified View\" has been added to the hierarchy for clarity. The
      reason for disabling settings in Play Mode is explained on Discord."
  - version: 1.3
    year: 2025
    month: 2
    day: 24
    details: "\u2022 Added the ability to save settings in the project, allowing
      settings to be transferred between computers. To enable saving settings in
      the project, go to Settings \u2192 Save In Project."
